Wash and dry produce. Drain @mango{4%ounce}(finely diced). Finely dice @roma tomato{1}(finely diced). Halve and peel @yellow onion{1}; thinly slice one half. Mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1} into strips.

> For 4 servings, thinly slice whole onion; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP. Use ¾ of the lemon for salsa.

== Mango Salsa ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine mango, tomato, minced onion, lemon zest, and juice from half the lemon. Season with @salt{to taste}.

== Smoky Sour Cream ==

In a separate small bowl, combine @smoked paprika{2%teaspoon} and @sour cream{4%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

== Charred Poblano ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano, sliced onion, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and lightly charred, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> Add a splash of water if veggies begin to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Beef ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @blackening spice{1%tablespoon}, and a big pinch of salt. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} and 2 TBSP water; bring to a simmer.

> For 4 servings, use 3 TBSP water instead of 2.

Return veggies to pan, stirring, until thoroughly combined. Taste and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> Add a splash or two of water, if necessary, until mixture is saucy.

== Tortillas ==

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{}. Microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

== To Serve ==

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with beef and veggie filling. Top with mango salsa and smoky sour cream. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.